post_text: It has come the attention of the district Administrative team that some families are able to view their child’s placement for the 2020-2021 school year. While the Parent Portal was slated to open today, that opening has been postponed until the end of business day on Monday, August 31st. This delay is a result of the numerous changes occurring due to social distancing regulations. Any information viewed prior to August 31st is incomplete and tentative. August 31st the portal will officially open for teacher assignments. We strongly encourage all families to check the portal for their placement information again on September 7th to ensure no further changes were made.

post_text:
Dear Parent(s)/Guardian(s):

I want to take this opportunity to inform you that tomorrow, Tuesday, August 25, 2020 will be the last day to request a transfer to the Virtual Academy until September 8, 2020. After the start of the school year parents again will be able to request a transfer to the Virtual Academy. As we prepare for the opening of school it was necessary to establish a cut-off date so that class lists can be finalized.

I apologize for any inconvenience and the late notice for the change in procedure.

post_text: The worldwide pandemic has created an unprecedented situation. It resulted in a Health Related School Closure for a portion of the 2019-2020 school year. While this unprecedented time has been stressful on all of us it has also highlighted the strength of the MERS community. We will continue to maximize our strength as a community to ensure the best possible education for your children. Currently, the district administrative team is working on multiple plans for the Fall of 2020. Decisions will be based on regulations set forth by the Governor but in order to plan accordingly, we need your help! You should have received an email from the district backpack. You can either complete the form from your email or click on the below link. We ask one submission per family regardless if you are using the link above or the one from your email. Lastly, complete this form by June 12th.
shared_text:

A Request by the Superintendent

post_text: Wemrock Brook was awarded their Sustainable NJ Schools Grant funded in partnership with the PSEG Foundation. The grant, Say No to Plastics! will create a plastic reduction campaign targeted toward disposable plastic water bottles and educate students on the importance of drinking water. It will fund the installation of a refillable water bottle station for the students!

post_text: Clark Mills second graders spent the past week reading and learning about people who have made a positive contribution to our community and the world at large. These people are ones that are considered to be heroes. So then the question was posed, “What are the characteristics of a hero?” Overwhelmingly, our students stated the characteristics of bravery, caring, kindness, giving, loving, and hard working as ones that a true hero possesses. As a culminating activity, the children were asked to choose a person or occupation that they felt exemplified the characteristics of a hero and to create a thank you. It was so heartwarming to hear and see the gratitude and appreciation that our kids have for all the nurses, doctors, firemen/women, first responders, and other essential workers that are keeping us safe during this difficult time.

Manalapan PBA Local #229
April 24 at 6:52 PM ·

The Manalapan Township PBA Local 229 would like to thank Charlie Lettice, one of our 5th graders from Clark Mills School for providing care packages containing paper products, sanitizers and other essential items to families in need within our community.

We would also like to thank Wegmans for providing food boxes ($100 each) for twenty families and to Target for providing toys and games for all.

Manalapan PBA Local #229
April 24 at 6:52 PM ·

The Manalapan Township PBA Local 229 would like to thank Charlie Lettice, one of our 5th graders from Clark Mills School for providing care packages containing paper products, sanitizers and other essential items to families in need within our community.

We would also like to thank Wegmans for providing food boxes ($100 each) for twenty families and to Target for providing toys and games for all.

post_text: Milford Brook School: In addition to our students continuing to spread kindness by chalking their walk, we have encouraged our students and their families to participate in our virtual wellness week. On Monday, students were sent Go Noodle Yoga links to help them relax, refresh, and reset. On Tuesday, we encouraged our students to practice expressing gratitude by taking a picture of (or writing about) someone or something they are grateful for. We cannot wait to see what Workout Wednesday and Free Choice Thursday bring. Students are encouraged to work out their bodies and their brains on Wednesday; and on Thursday, they were given examples of ways to practice wellness (i.e. color, read a book, create a calming jar, dance, etc.).

post_text: Tonight we bring you an updated message regarding our schedule. All district buildings except for MEMS will remain closed until further notice. District business will be conducted through MEMS THREE days a week (M,W,&F). While we have limited staff working onsite, the best form of communication is e-mail. The same visiting security protocols are still applicable. Please email your building administrator before planning a visit.

post_text:
I want to take a moment to update you on the incident which took place on Thursday, March 12th. The Manalapan Police with the assistance of the MERS school district have identified the woman involved in Thursday’s incident. They have spoken to her and have concluded she did not have any ill intentions. I am thankful for the work of the Manalapan Police Department and the partnership we have with them.

Respectfully,
Rich Oppegaard
Director of School Safety & Security

post_text: After consulting with the Manalapan Health Department, we have decided to close all of our schools from Monday, March 16th, through Friday, March 27th. We will use a "snow day" on Monday, March 16th. Please use this day as practice to log onto Classlink. Log onto the parent portal (https://parents.mersnj.us) and click on the documents tab for more details regarding Classlink and your child's login information. MERS virtual distant learning days will begin on Tuesday, March 17th. If you have any issues please contact your building principal.

post_text:
Good afternoon MERS family,

This afternoon we had an incident at Milford Brook regarding a suspicious female taking a video of students playing on the field with her phone. The security officer at the school responded and following protocol the Manalapan Police and I were notified, and responded. The Manalapan Police checked the area and are handling the matter. Should you have any questions or concerns please feel free contact the Manalapan Police or myself.

Respectfully,

Richard Oppegaard
Director of School safety & Security
